    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Loading dose of dexmedetomidine is related hemodynamic instability such as bradycardia and
      hypertension.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesized substitution of loading of dexmedetomidine for midazolam could
      reduce hemodynamic instability during spinal anesthesia for knee arthroscopy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
